The paper focuses on the usability of two-factor authentication (2F) technologies, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The study also involves conducting a survey to measure the usability of different 2F solutions, which is a research method commonly used in human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social computing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of context and motivation on perceived usability, which relates to the field of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE).
